## Previous Task: Split-Tier Architecture (Linux Web Host + MacBook Compute Node)

### Problem
Linux server has NVIDIA GTX 1060 3GB Pascal GPU — incompatible with PyTorch 2.4+ cuDNN 9.x. Also insufficient VRAM for Docling's RT-DETR model. MacBook (Apple Silicon) can run Docling on CPU/MPS and Ollama on Neural Engine/Metal.

### Solution
Keep public website on always-on Linux machine, offload PDF processing (Docling) and LLM inference (Ollama) to MacBook over Tailscale VPN (100.x.x.x). No open firewall ports on MacBook.

### New Architecture
- Linux Server: Public-facing Flask app, SQLite, NGINX/Gunicorn. No GPU needed.
- MacBook: FastAPI + Docling PDF microservice (port 8000), Ollama (port 11434). Bound to Tailscale IP only.
- Network: Tailscale WireGuard VPN for encrypted, NAT-traversing connectivity.

### Progress
