## Previous Task: Fix Processing Status & Loading Bar

### Problem
After upload, the document status immediately shows "Completed" once the remote PDF extraction returns, but the LLM call for PO extraction may still be running. The user sees incomplete/missing PO data. The loading UI is just a small spinner in the badge — not informative enough for a multi-stage process.

### Solution
Introduce a multi-stage status: `processing` (PDF extraction) → `analyzing` (LLM PO extraction) → `completed` (done). Update the frontend to show a determinate progress bar with stage labels. Poll until `completed` or `error`.

### Plan
[X] Add new status value `analyzing` to backend (app.py)
[X] Update `process_pdf()` to set `analyzing` before LLM call and `completed` after
[X] Ensure error handling covers both PDF and LLM stages
[X] Update frontend badgeHTML() to show stage labels and a progress bar
[X] Add CSS for determinate progress bar and stage colors
[X] Update polling logic to keep polling through `analyzing`
[X] Test end-to-end upload flow

## Previous Task: Redesign Document Detail View

### Problem
The document detail view uses tabs (PDF / PO Data) which hides one view at a time. Users want to see both the PDF and extracted PO data simultaneously side-by-side. Also, the current "Save Corrections" flow is always editable — users want a read-only display with an explicit Edit mode, plus the ability to add/delete items.

### Solution
Replace tabs with side-by-side panels: PDF on the left, PO Data on the right. Default to read-only display. Add an Edit button that toggles edit mode with inline inputs. In edit mode, support adding new items and deleting existing items. Save all changes at once via the existing corrections endpoint.

### Plan
[X] Update HTML template: replace tabs with detail-panels (pdf-panel + po-panel)
[X] Add CSS: side-by-side grid layout, panel styles, read-only/edit modes, responsive stacking
[X] Update JS openDocument(): render PDF iframe and PO data simultaneously
[X] Add JS togglePOEditMode(): switch between read-only and editable views
[X] Update JS renderPOReadOnly(): display meta grid + item table without inputs
[X] Update JS renderPOEditMode(): display inputs, add delete button per row
[X] Add JS addNewItemRow(): dynamically append empty item row with temp ID
[X] Update JS saveCorrections(): collect DELETE_ITEM and ADD_ITEM operations
[X] Extend backend /api/purchase-orders/correct: handle DELETE_ITEM and ADD_ITEM
[X] Test end-to-end: view PDF + PO side-by-side, edit, add item, delete item, save

## Previous Task: Re-extract & Duplicate Detection

### Problem
Users need a way to re-run LLM PO extraction on an existing document if the initial extraction was poor. Also, uploading the same PDF twice creates duplicate documents.

### Solution
Add a "Re-extract" button in the PO Data panel that re-runs PO extraction without re-uploading. Detect duplicate uploads by content hash and prompt the user to view existing or re-process.

### Plan
